Japanese trading house Nichimen Corp. said Thursday  its pre-tax earnings tumbled 29.1 percent to 12.4 billion yen (120 million  dollars) in the year to March as sales declined.
The affiliate of Sanwa Bank Ltd. said sales dropped 9.3 percent to 5,488  billion yen, depressed in all sectors except machinery.
Nichimen projected a further decline in earnings to 10 billion yen for the  current year but forecast increased sales of 5,500 billion yen.
